# <span id="7">7</span>

>     H?' se ku'pros kai` Pa'fos h?` Pa'normos

If thee, Cyprus or Paphos or Panormos \[holds\].

This is from Strabo, early first century A.D. Panormos was a frequent
name, and does not refer to Palermo, which was not founded in Sappho's
time.

