# <span id="11">11</span>

>     ... Ta'de nu^n e?tai'rais
>     tai^s e?'maisi te'rpna ka'lws a?ei'sw.

This will I now sing skilfully to please my friends.

Athanaeus quotes this to show that there is not necessarily any reproach
in the word e?tai'rai. Like many others, the fragment is unfortunately
too short for anything but a literal translation. The breathing of the
word in question in Attic Greek would of course be rough.

