# <span id="17">17</span>

>     ... kat? e?'mon sta'lagmon,
>     to`n d? e?pipla'zontes a?'moi fe'roien
>          kai` meledw'nais.

From my distress: let buffeting winds bear it and all care away.

From the "Etymologicum Magnum" to show the Aeolic use of z in place of
ss. Bergk conjectures a?'moi for a?'nemoi, "winds". The fragment is
tantilizingly incomplete, as so many others are, and the reading of one
or two words in not certain.

